        </div>

        <div class="comp-map">
          <div class="camp camp-legacy">
            <div class="camp-label">Camp A · Legacy CRM-native MAPs</div>
            <h3>Built in 2010 for a Salesforce-only world.</h3>
            <p>Data model designed when CRM was the only source of truth and email was the only channel. Cannot ingest warehouse data or product events natively. Customers stay out of switching cost, not love.</p>
            <ul class="camp-list">
              <li><strong>Marketo</strong><span>Adobe fatigue</span></li>
              <li><strong>HubSpot</strong><span>Going upmarket</span></li>
              <li><strong>SFMC</strong><span>B2C DNA in B2B</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="camp camp-modern">
            <div class="camp-label">Camp B · Modern point tools</div>
            <h3>Solve one slice. Leave three holes.</h3>
            <p>Warehouse-aware but architecturally narrow. Each one forces the customer into a patchwork of three or four other tools to run a real marketing motion. A platform need met with a collection.</p>
            <ul class="camp-list">
              <li><strong>Hightouch</strong><span>No campaign layer</span></li>
              <li><strong>Iterable</strong><span>B2C-first</span></li>
              <li><strong>Customer.io</strong><span>PLG graduation cliff</span></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

